ce:section.ce:para:
We used the B3LYP/6–31++G(d,p) functional in the gas phase under the same temperature and pressure conditions to calculate the zero point vibrational energy (ZPVE), heat capacity (
C v
), entropy (S), enthalpy (H), Gibbs free energy (G), and internal thermal energy (U) in order to predict the thermodynamic parameters of the studied systems. Table 7 has a list of all standard properties. Our findings demonstrate that the investigated compounds' computed enthalpy and Gibbs free energy are all negative, indicating that they are thermodynamically stable. In all systems doped with the nitrogen atom, we also find a decrease in Gibbs free energy, a rise in entropy, and a heat capacity at constant volume when compared to the basic systems.
